                <h1>Understanding Hades: The Greek God of the Underworld</h1>
                <p>Hades, the Greek god of the underworld, ruled over the realm of the dead and was the brother of Zeus and Poseidon. Often misunderstood, he is not the god of evil but rather a guardian of the afterlife, ensuring that souls receive their just rewards. His three-headed dog, Cerberus, guards the gates of the underworld.</p>
